title: Search Download and Handle Data from Copernicus Marine Service Information
text: package provides interface R Copernicus Marine services. Note services need account comply specific terms. usage section briefly shows three different ways obtaining data Copernicus: Downloading subset Downloading full dataset Using WMTS server Please check manual complete documentation package. Unfortunately, downloading subsets operational R due technical issues. seems might take time get fixed. meantime, look work-around. don’t want subset data want complete set, can use SpatioTemporal Asset Catalogs (STAC), available product. First can list STAC files available specific product (layer): Downloading first file can done cms_download_stac(stac_files[1,,drop = FALSE], tempdir()), file stored temporary directory. default progress printed files can large may take time download. Web Map Tile Services (WMTS) allow quickly plot pre-rendered images onto map. may useful need data analyses handy quick visualisations, inspection presentation data. R easy add WMTS layers interactive map using leaflet widgets. demonstrated example (note documentation map shown statically interactive).

The time series is aggregated in time in order to reach a two full year’s time series sliding window.

This product includes daily and monthly mean files of temperature, salinity, currents, sea level, mixed layer depth and ice parameters from the top to the bottom over the global ocean. It also includes hourly mean surface fields for sea level height, temperature and currents. The global ocean output files are displayed with a 1/12 degree horizontal resolution with regular longitude/latitude equirectangular projection.

50 vertical levels are ranging from 0 to 5500 meters.

This product also delivers a special dataset for surface current which also includes wave and tidal drift called SMOC (Surface merged Ocean Current).

$GetRecordByIdResponse$MD_Metadata$identificationInfo$MD_DataIdentification$abstract$CharacterString[[1]] #> [1] "'''Short description'''

The Operational Mercator global ocean analysis and forecast system at 1/12 degree is providing 10 days of 3D global ocean forecasts updated daily. The time series is aggregated in time in order to reach a two full year’s time series sliding window.

This product includes daily and monthly mean files of temperature, salinity, currents, sea level, mixed layer depth and ice parameters from the top to the bottom over the global ocean. It also includes hourly mean surface fields for sea level height, temperature and currents. The global ocean output files are displayed with a 1/12 degree horizontal resolution with regular longitude/latitude equirectangular projection.

50 vertical levels are ranging from 0 to 5500 meters.

This product also delivers a special dataset for surface current which also includes wave and tidal drift called SMOC (Surface merged Ocean Current).

code: cms_download_stac(   file_tibble,   destination,   show_progress = TRUE,   overwrite = FALSE )  cms_list_stac_files(product, layer)  cms_stac_properties(product, layer)

title: List and get STAC files for a Copernicus marine product — cms_download_stac
text: file_tibble dplyr::tibble() row files downloaded. created cms_list_stac_files(). destination character string representing path location downloaded files stored. show_progress logical value. TRUE (default) download progress shown. can useful large files. overwrite logical value. FALSE (default), files destination overwritten exist. Instead error thrown case. set TRUE, existing files overwritten. product identifier (type character) desired Copernicus marine product. Can obtained cms_products_list. layer name desired layer within product (type character). Can obtained cms_product_details.

title: List and get STAC files for a Copernicus marine product — cms_download_stac
text: case cms_stac_properties dplyr::tibble() returned product properties, used precursor cms_list_stac_files. case cms_list_stac_files dplyr::tibble() returned containing available URLs (specified product layer) meta information returned. case cms_download_stac invisible logical value returned, indicating whether requested files successfully stored destination path. list responses (class httr2::response()) requested download links included attribute result.

title: List and get STAC files for a Copernicus marine product — cms_download_stac
text: Pepijn de Vries

title: List and get STAC files for a Copernicus marine product — cms_download_stac
code: if (FALSE) { # \dontrun{ ## List some STAC properties for a specific product and layer cms_stac_properties(   product       = "GLOBAL_ANALYSISFORECAST_PHY_001_024",   layer         = "cmems_mod_glo_phy-cur_anfc_0.083deg_P1D-m" )  ## Get the available files for a specific product and layer: file_tibble <-   cms_list_stac_files("GLOBAL_ANALYSISFORECAST_PHY_001_024",                       "cmems_mod_glo_phy-cur_anfc_0.083deg_P1D-m")  dest <- tempdir()  ## download the first file from the file_tibble to 'dest' cms_download_stac(file_tibble[1,, drop = FALSE], dest) } # }

title: Obtain a WMTS entry for specific Copernicus marine products and add to a leaflet map — cms_wmts_details
text: Functions retrieving Web Map Tile Services information specific products, layers variables add leaflet map.

title: Obtain a WMTS entry for specific Copernicus marine products and add to a leaflet map — cms_wmts_details
code: cms_wmts_details(product, layer, variable)  addCmsWMTSTiles(   map,   product,   layer,   variable,   tilematrixset = "EPSG:3857",   options = leaflet::WMSTileOptions(format = "image/png", transparent = TRUE),   ... )  cms_wmts_get_capabilities(product, layer, variable, type = c("list", "xml"))

title: Obtain a WMTS entry for specific Copernicus marine products and add to a leaflet map — cms_wmts_details
text: product identifier (type character) desired Copernicus marine product. Can obtained cms_products_list. layer name desired layer within product (type character). Can obtained cms_product_details. variable name desired variable specific layer product (type character). Can obtained cms_product_details. map map widget object created leaflet::leaflet() tilematrixset character string representing tilematrixset used. many cases "EPSG:3857" (Pseudo-Mercator) "EPSG:4326" (World Geodetic System 1984) available, checked cms_wmts_details. options Passed leaflet::addWMSTiles(). ... Passed leaflet::addWMSTiles(). type character string indicating whether capabilities returned "list" (default) "xml" (xml2::xml_new_document()).

title: Obtain a WMTS entry for specific Copernicus marine products and add to a leaflet map — cms_wmts_details
text: cms_wmts_details returns tibble detains WMTS service. cms_wmts_getcapabilities returns either list xml_document depending value type. AddCmsWMTSTiles returns leaflet map updated requested tiles.
